menu "CzechMate firmware"

config CHESS_ENABLE_TEST_TASK
    bool "Enable automated test task"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, creates test_task (4 KB stack) and the test command queue.
        Disable for production builds to save RAM and reduce background logging;
        hardware/UART test commands that depend on the task will not run.

config CHESS_ENABLE_WEB_SERVER
    bool "Enable HTTP web server (WiFi AP/STA UI + REST)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, builds the full web_server_task HTTP stack: WiFi hotspot/STA
        bootstrap, REST API, WebSocket, embedded piece PNGs, and browser-facing
        routes.

        When disabled, the web_server_task component is still linked as a lightweight
        BLE/remote bridge (JSON dispatch, game snapshots, opening trainer API over BLE).
        Flash and RAM savings: no esp_http_server, no mDNS, no embedded PNG assets,
        no HTTP handler sources.

        Use BLE + UART builds for factory test or minimal firmware profiles.
        Reconfigure after change: idf.py fullclean reconfigure build

endmenu
